  <entry>
    <title>Claude Code Cheat Sheet</title>
    <link href="/2026/03/02/claudeCodeCheatsheet/"/>
    <url>/2026/03/02/claudeCodeCheatsheet/</url>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>A quick reference for the Claude Code CLI. Covers the commands I use most, how to wire up hooks, define skills, and spin up subagents.</p><!-- more --><hr><h2 id="Slash-Commands"><a href="#Slash-Commands" class="headerlink" title="Slash Commands"></a>Slash Commands</h2><p>Run these in the Claude Code prompt:</p><table><thead><tr><th>Command</th><th>What it does</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>/help</code></td><td>Show all available commands</td></tr><tr><td><code>/clear</code></td><td>Clear conversation history</td></tr><tr><td><code>/compact</code></td><td>Compact context to save tokens</td></tr><tr><td><code>/cost</code></td><td>Show token usage and cost for the session</td></tr><tr><td><code>/status</code></td><td>Show current model and config</td></tr><tr><td><code>/model</code></td><td>Switch model</td></tr><tr><td><code>/memory</code></td><td>View and manage persistent memory</td></tr><tr><td><code>/fast</code></td><td>Toggle fast mode (Opus 4 with faster output)</td></tr><tr><td><code>/review-pr</code></td><td>Review a pull request (if skill defined)</td></tr><tr><td><code>/commit</code></td><td>Commit staged changes (if skill defined)</td></tr></tbody></table><blockquote><p>Slash commands prefixed with <code>/</code> that aren’t built-in are <strong>skills</strong> — more on those below.</p></blockquote><hr><h2 id="Hooks"><a href="#Hooks" class="headerlink" title="Hooks"></a>Hooks</h2><p>Hooks run shell commands automatically when Claude takes certain actions. Configure them in <code>.claude/settings.json</code>:</p><figure class="highlight json"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs json"><span class="hljs-punctuation">&#123;</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">&quot;hooks&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-punctuation">&#123;</span><br>    <span class="hljs-attr">&quot;user-prompt-submit-hook&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-punctuation">&#123;</span><br>      <span class="hljs-attr">&quot;command&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-string">&quot;echo &#x27;User submitted a prompt&#x27;&quot;</span><br>    <span class="hljs-punctuation">&#125;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">,</span><br>    <span class="hljs-attr">&quot;pre-tool-use&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-punctuation">&#123;</span><br>      <span class="hljs-attr">&quot;command&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-string">&quot;echo &#x27;About to call a tool&#x27;&quot;</span><br>    <span class="hljs-punctuation">&#125;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">,</span><br>    <span class="hljs-attr">&quot;post-tool-use&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-punctuation">&#123;</span><br>      <span class="hljs-attr">&quot;command&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-string">&quot;echo &#x27;Tool call finished&#x27;&quot;</span><br>    <span class="hljs-punctuation">&#125;</span><br>  <span class="hljs-punctuation">&#125;</span><br><span class="hljs-punctuation">&#125;</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="Common-hook-events"><a href="#Common-hook-events" class="headerlink" title="Common hook events"></a>Common hook events</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Event</th><th>Fires when</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>user-prompt-submit-hook</code></td><td>User sends a message</td></tr><tr><td><code>pre-tool-use</code></td><td>Before any tool call</td></tr><tr><td><code>post-tool-use</code></td><td>After any tool call</td></tr><tr><td><code>stop</code></td><td>Claude finishes responding</td></tr></tbody></table><h3 id="Practical-examples"><a href="#Practical-examples" class="headerlink" title="Practical examples"></a>Practical examples</h3><p><strong>Auto-format on file edit:</strong></p><figure class="highlight json"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs json"><span class="hljs-attr">&quot;post-tool-use&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-punctuation">&#123;</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">&quot;command&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-string">&quot;npx prettier --write .&quot;</span><br><span class="hljs-punctuation">&#125;</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p><strong>Notify on finish:</strong></p><figure class="highlight json"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs json"><span class="hljs-attr">&quot;stop&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-punctuation">&#123;</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">&quot;command&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-string">&quot;osascript -e &#x27;display notification \&quot;Claude is done\&quot; with title \&quot;Claude Code\&quot;&#x27;&quot;</span><br><span class="hljs-punctuation">&#125;</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p><strong>Block dangerous commands (pre-tool-use guard):</strong><br>Hooks that exit with a non-zero code will block the tool call and send the output back to Claude as feedback — useful for enforcing rules.</p><hr><h2 id="Skills"><a href="#Skills" class="headerlink" title="Skills"></a>Skills</h2><p>Skills are reusable prompt templates stored as markdown files in <code>.claude/skills/</code>. They become slash commands.</p><h3 id="File-structure"><a href="#File-structure" class="headerlink" title="File structure"></a>File structure</h3><figure class="highlight dos"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs dos">.claude/<br>  skills/<br>    commit.<span class="hljs-built_in">md</span><br>    review-pr.<span class="hljs-built_in">md</span><br>    deploy.<span class="hljs-built_in">md</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h3 id="Example-skill-commit"><a href="#Example-skill-commit" class="headerlink" title="Example skill: /commit"></a>Example skill: <code>/commit</code></h3><p><strong>.claude&#x2F;skills&#x2F;commit.md:</strong></p><figure class="highlight markdown"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs markdown">---<br><span class="hljs-section">description: Stage and commit all changes with a generated message</span><br><span class="hljs-section">---</span><br><br><span class="hljs-bullet">1.</span> Run <span class="hljs-code">`git diff --staged`</span> and <span class="hljs-code">`git status`</span> to see what changed.<br><span class="hljs-bullet">2.</span> Write a concise commit message summarizing the changes.<br><span class="hljs-bullet">3.</span> Run <span class="hljs-code">`git add -A &amp;&amp; git commit -m &quot;&lt;message&gt;&quot;`</span>.<br><span class="hljs-bullet">4.</span> Show the commit hash when done.<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Invoke it with <code>/commit</code> in the Claude Code prompt.</p><h3 id="Passing-arguments-to-skills"><a href="#Passing-arguments-to-skills" class="headerlink" title="Passing arguments to skills"></a>Passing arguments to skills</h3><p>Skills receive arguments via <code>args</code>:</p><figure class="highlight markdown"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs markdown">---<br><span class="hljs-section">description: Review a GitHub PR</span><br><span class="hljs-section">---</span><br><br>Review PR #&#123;&#123; args &#125;&#125; — fetch with <span class="hljs-code">`gh pr view &#123;&#123; args &#125;&#125; --json ...`</span><br>and summarize the changes, highlight risks, and suggest improvements.<br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Usage: <code>/review-pr 123</code></p><hr><h2 id="Subagents-Task-Tool"><a href="#Subagents-Task-Tool" class="headerlink" title="Subagents (Task Tool)"></a>Subagents (Task Tool)</h2><p>Subagents let Claude spin up specialized agents for complex subtasks. Claude Code comes with several built-in types.</p><h3 id="Built-in-agent-types"><a href="#Built-in-agent-types" class="headerlink" title="Built-in agent types"></a>Built-in agent types</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Best for</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>Bash</code></td><td>Git operations, running commands</td></tr><tr><td><code>Explore</code></td><td>Codebase search, finding files&#x2F;patterns</td></tr><tr><td><code>Plan</code></td><td>Designing implementation strategies</td></tr><tr><td><code>general-purpose</code></td><td>Multi-step research tasks</td></tr><tr><td><code>claude-code-guide</code></td><td>Questions about Claude Code itself</td></tr></tbody></table><h3 id="Basic-usage-in-a-skill-or-prompt"><a href="#Basic-usage-in-a-skill-or-prompt" class="headerlink" title="Basic usage (in a skill or prompt)"></a>Basic usage (in a skill or prompt)</h3><p>Claude calls the Task tool internally. You can instruct it explicitly:</p><blockquote><p>“Use the Explore agent to find all API endpoint definitions, then use the Bash agent to run the tests.”</p></blockquote><h3 id="Key-options"><a href="#Key-options" class="headerlink" title="Key options"></a>Key options</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>What it does</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>run_in_background: true</code></td><td>Fire-and-forget; check output later</td></tr><tr><td><code>isolation: &quot;worktree&quot;</code></td><td>Run in an isolated git worktree</td></tr><tr><td><code>resume: &quot;&lt;agent-id&gt;&quot;</code></td><td>Resume a previous agent with its context</td></tr></tbody></table><h3 id="Parallel-agents"><a href="#Parallel-agents" class="headerlink" title="Parallel agents"></a>Parallel agents</h3><p>When tasks are independent, Claude runs multiple agents at once:</p><blockquote><p>“Search for all usages of <code>getUser</code> and simultaneously check for any open GitHub issues related to auth.”</p></blockquote><p>This launches two agents in a single message — one Explore, one Bash — and merges the results.</p><hr><h2 id="Settings-Reference"><a href="#Settings-Reference" class="headerlink" title="Settings Reference"></a>Settings Reference</h2><p><code>.claude/settings.json</code> controls permissions, hooks, and environment:</p><figure class="highlight json"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><code class="hljs json"><span class="hljs-punctuation">&#123;</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">&quot;model&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-string">&quot;claude-opus-4-6&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">,</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">&quot;hooks&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-punctuation">&#123;</span> ... <span class="hljs-punctuation">&#125;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">,</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">&quot;allowedTools&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-punctuation">[</span><span class="hljs-string">&quot;Bash&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">,</span> <span class="hljs-string">&quot;Read&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">,</span> <span class="hljs-string">&quot;Edit&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">,</span> <span class="hljs-string">&quot;Write&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">]</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">,</span><br>  <span class="hljs-attr">&quot;env&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-punctuation">&#123;</span><br>    <span class="hljs-attr">&quot;NODE_ENV&quot;</span><span class="hljs-punctuation">:</span> <span class="hljs-string">&quot;development&quot;</span><br>  <span class="hljs-punctuation">&#125;</span><br><span class="hljs-punctuation">&#125;</span><br></code></pre></td></tr></table></figure><hr><h2 id="Tips"><a href="#Tips" class="headerlink" title="Tips"></a>Tips</h2><ul><li>Use <code>/compact</code> aggressively on long sessions — it preserves task context while freeing up the token window.</li><li>Skills + hooks together are powerful: a <code>/deploy</code> skill can trigger a post-hook that posts to Slack.</li><li>Worktree isolation (<code>isolation: &quot;worktree&quot;</code>) is great for risky refactors — changes are thrown away if you decide not to keep them.</li><li>The <code>Explore</code> subagent is much cheaper on context than running many Grep&#x2F;Glob calls yourself for open-ended searches.</li></ul>]]></content>
    
    
    
